-- Alstom Evaluates Buying Repower From Suzlon, FT Deutschland Says
-- B y   R i c h a r d   W e i s s
-- 2012-03-13T20:35:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-13/alstom-evaluates-buying-repower-from-suzlon-ft-deutschland-says.html
Alstom SA (ALO)  is evaluating a potential
offer for Repower Systems SE, the German wind turbine maker
owned by  Suzlon Energy Ltd. (SUEL)  of  India ,  Financial Times
Deutschland  said, without saying where it got the information.  Alstom has started talks with Suzlon, which may be willing
to sell the unit for 1.5 billion euros ($2 billion), and Alstom
has been granted exclusive access to performance data on the
unit, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Richard Weiss in Frankfurt at 
 rweiss5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net  